What you need to know:

JM Kariuki who “tanga-tangad” around with a sack full of cash and gave out hoes and mattocks.In his own words, DP Ruto was a hustler hawking kienyenji chicken at a place called Turbo near Eldoret town.Then President Moi “discovered” him and put him in a “hustler” outfit called Youth for Kanu 1992 (YK‘92).